title: FOIL Method
text: The F stands for First, where we multiply the first component of each terms first. $$y^2 y$$

title: FOIL Method
text: The O stands for Outer, where we multiply the first component of the second term with the $$\frac{second}{outer}$$ component of the second term. $$y^2 \left(-9\right)$$

title: FOIL Method
text: The I stands for Inner, where we multiply the inner components. $$7y$$

title: FOIL Method
text: The L stands for Last, where we multiply the last component of each terms. $$7\left(-9\right)$$
